CHILE DAYBOOK: Central Bank Discloses Bi-weekly Traders Survey

-- B y   R a n d y   W o o d s
-- 
2011-05-25T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/chile-daybook-central-bank-discloses-bi-weekly-traders-survey.html
Chile ’s central bank discloses
results of its bi-weekly survey of traders and investors on the
bank’s website at 8:30 a.m. New York time.  EQUITIES:
*The Ipsa index fell 0.2 percent to 4,790.38.
*Empresas Iansa SA rose 4.5 percent to 49.1 pesos, the steepest
increase in eight weeks. Chile’s largest sugar producer rose
along with sugar prices gains in New York.
*Empresas La Polar SA fell 1.4 percent to 2,602.1 pesos, capping
a record tenth straight day of losses, according to data
compiled by Bloomberg. The department-store operator had its
 credit rating  cut last week to BBB+ from A- at Feller Rate,
which cited increased loan portfolio risk.  MARKETS:
*Chile’s peso strengthened as rebounding copper prices signaled
an increased trade surplus and gains in global equities
bolstered investor appetite for riskier, emerging market assets.
The peso rose 0.3 percent to 471.95 per  U.S. dollar .
*Chile’s central bank paid an average of 471.39 per U.S. dollar
for $50 million, as part of a $12 billion effort to limit the
peso’s gains, according to data published on the bank’s website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
